# Git commit messages

- **Always use English** for commit message title and body.
- Do not use Arabic or other non-Latin scripts in commit messages.
- Use clear, short imperative style (e.g. "Add points breakdown popup", "Fix share image capture").
- This avoids issues with deployment pipelines, CI, and "Made-with" metadata that expect ASCII/English.
